Adam Heath wrote:
> However, compiling for stable kernels should always give you a sane
> environment.  With debian, are glibc is currently compiled against
> 2.2.13(well, in potato).
You're forgetting just how /old/ the 2.2 kernels are.  So many new
devices, so many new device drivers :-)
> Anyone compiling and writing utility progs for unstable kernels needs
> to know that having to upgrade to the latest unstable kernel is not
> always possible(1).
However, having to upgrade to the most stable kernel in the last 3
months is not unreasonable if a particular program needs a particular device.
